parameters.name: errors
parameters.description: An iterable of errors, may not actually be Error instances.

parameters.name: message
parameters.description: An optional human-readable description of the aggregate error.

parameters.name: options
parameters.description:
An object that has the following properties:

cause Optional


          A property indicating the specific cause of the error.
          When catching and re-throwing an error with a more-specific or useful error message, this property can be used to pass the original error.

name: AggregateError.prototype.constructor
description: The constructor function that created the instance object. For AggregateError instances, the initial value is the AggregateError constructor.

name: AggregateError.prototype.name
description: Represents the name for the type of error. For AggregateError.prototype.name, the initial value is "AggregateError".

name: errors
description: An array representing the errors that were aggregated.
